00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:25,391
{\an8}MIYAKE POSTS "I CONSTANTLY ASK MYSELF"

115
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,394
{\an8}<i>We asked Miyake what he meant.</i>

116
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:33,132
In this day and age, people say

117
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:38,371
it's never too late to start something
no matter how old you are.

118
00:10:38,437 --> 00:10:39,639
But...

119
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:44,043
For men, their thirties and forties

120
00:10:45,678 --> 00:10:49,849
are sort of a turning point, so if I...

121
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:54,587
If I want to move on to the next stage,

122
00:10:55,955 --> 00:11:00,326
I can't help but feel that
my forties is my last chance.

123
00:11:00,393 --> 00:11:01,927
I think we all feel that.

124
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:03,996
What do we do from now?

125
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:07,400
Who are we living for?

126
00:11:07,466 --> 00:11:10,569
Do we live for someone else?
Or for our own selves?

127
00:11:10,636 --> 00:11:13,673
I've been thinking about it
since I was 30.

128
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:18,811
I think about it as
a separate thing from the six of us.

129
00:11:18,878 --> 00:11:23,382
I bet the others
individually think about it, too

130
00:11:23,449 --> 00:11:26,686
about how they want to
live their own lives.

131
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:32,058
That's what I meant when I wrote,
"I constantly ask myself."

132
00:11:32,124 --> 00:11:33,459
What do I want to do?

