149
00:12:39,158 --> 00:12:42,661
Okay, let's do it with the music.
Please play "TL."

150
00:12:48,033 --> 00:12:53,172
<i>For this livestream show,
they dared to take on a great challenge.</i>

151
00:12:59,678 --> 00:13:04,717
<i>Performing their song "TL"
without vocals, just by dancing.</i>

152
00:13:16,028 --> 00:13:17,129
Okay...

153
00:13:17,196 --> 00:13:19,165
In the structure,

154
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:25,971
I want to show V6's dance
as a work of art.

155
00:13:26,038 --> 00:13:30,509
So maybe like a water burst
or the water goes back, I don't know.

156
00:13:30,576 --> 00:13:35,114
I want something to make people feel
it's moved up another gear

157
00:13:35,681 --> 00:13:38,751
just when they think
it peaked at the dance.

158
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:42,688
The water should be put in
at the right time or it'll be slippery.

159
00:13:42,755 --> 00:13:45,391
{\an8}-That could ruin it.
-It'll be very slippery.

160
00:13:45,457 --> 00:13:47,927
{\an8}When you know it'll be slippery,

161
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:51,363
{\an8}you can't dance as hard as you can.

162
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:53,666
Another thing that I'm wondering about

163
00:13:53,732 --> 00:13:56,735
is whether you should wear shoes
or go barefoot.

164
00:13:56,802 --> 00:13:58,070
Barefoot.

165
00:13:58,137 --> 00:14:00,139
-Are you sure?
-I think it's better.

166
00:14:00,639 --> 00:14:03,108
You mean we'll be barefoot before that?

167
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:04,710
No, that's why...

168
00:14:04,777 --> 00:14:07,613
-We'll take them off.
-Remove and align them?

169
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:10,249
-We don't need that bit.
-No?

170
00:14:10,316 --> 00:14:12,952
No, we don't need it.

171
00:14:13,018 --> 00:14:14,820
That's what my father taught me.

172
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:15,788
Good manners.

173
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:17,656
Like full of energy...

174
00:14:17,723 --> 00:14:22,494
<i>During the meeting, another thing that
the members were very particular about</i>

175
00:14:22,561 --> 00:14:24,830
<i>was the structure of their visual book.</i>

176
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:28,334
<i>Whether or not to include
the members' interviews.</i>

177
00:14:31,837 --> 00:14:35,107
Do you really want to include them?

178
00:14:36,475 --> 00:14:39,578
Because it's not a pamphlet, right?

179
00:14:40,679 --> 00:14:42,147
It's a visual book.

180
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:47,052
I thought people can feel "25 years"
more without words.

181
00:14:47,119 --> 00:14:48,787
I'm sorry, but I think

182
00:14:48,854 --> 00:14:54,627
what we have in mind for this one is not
an image of us that's been fabricated.

183
00:14:54,693 --> 00:14:58,597
We want something more raw,
something that's more revealing.

184
00:14:58,664 --> 00:15:02,301
I want to choose photos that show

185
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:05,938
how a group of real people made it happen.

186
00:15:06,005 --> 00:15:08,574
Like pictures of us sweating.

187
00:15:09,141 --> 00:15:13,779
In other words, we want to shoot photos
that prove what we've done.

188
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:18,918
What does it take
to be an idol for 25 years?

189
00:15:18,984 --> 00:15:22,554
There must be something to it.

190
00:15:22,621 --> 00:15:26,025
Okada started taking pictures,

191
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:30,095
but I think what we need are
photos taken from that kind of distance.

192
00:15:31,497 --> 00:15:36,435
He's at a distance that no one else
can be at because he's a member.

193
00:15:36,502 --> 00:15:38,270
So those photos are special.

194
00:15:38,337 --> 00:15:39,805
Why not use those photos?

195
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,608
These photos when you're taken...

196
00:15:44,376 --> 00:15:46,679
It's like, "Please make me look nice."

197
00:15:46,745 --> 00:15:49,348
So the atmosphere's not the same.

198
00:15:50,816 --> 00:15:51,850
Too close.

199
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:58,190
<i>Just the way they are now.</i>

